# Builtin skills and workspace copy

Some built-in skills are duplicated at the repository root under [`skills/<name>/`](skills/) (e.g. [`skills/schedule-job/`](skills/schedule-job/)) so CLI paths and docs like `python3 skills/schedule-job/schedule_helper.py` work from a checkout.

**Rule:** When you edit anything under [`builtin_skills/<skill-name>/`](builtin_skills/), apply the **same change** to [`skills/<skill-name>/`](skills/) in the **same commit** (or immediately after). The [`builtin_skills/`](builtin_skills/) tree remains the canonical packaged copy; [`skills/`](skills/) is the workspace mirror for operators.

If you add a new mirrored skill, add its directory under both trees and mention it here.
